# Coding Standards — {{TEAM_NAME}}
_Maintained by Forge and Vigil._

## Language Standards
- Python: PEP 8, type hints required, docstrings for all public functions
- TypeScript: strict mode, explicit return types
- Bash: `set -euo pipefail` on all scripts

## Testing
- All non-trivial functions must have tests
- TDD preferred: write failing test first
- Test coverage target: 80%+

## Code Review Checklist
- [ ] Follows spec exactly
- [ ] Tests written and passing
- [ ] Error cases handled
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] Docstrings/comments for complex logic

## Git Standards
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- One commit per logical change
- PR descriptions follow STAR format

